
[1]soliloquy

   SOLIL'OQUY, n. [L. solus, alone, and loquor, to speak.]

   1. A talking to one's self; a talking or discourse of a person alone,
   or not addressed to another person, even when others are persent.
   Lovers are always allowed the comfort of soliloquy.

   2. A written composition, reciting what it is supposed a person speaks
   to himself. The whole poem is a solioquy.
